{"blocks":[{"key":"dqv2s","text":"Take 50 µL of competent cells in a sterile Eppendorf tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d8aq4","text":"Add 2~5 µL of the plasmid to be transformed into each tube, gently mix the plasmid and competent cells with a pipette tip, and ice bath for 25 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7qrgl","text":"Heat shock the ice-bath mixture in a 42℃ water bath for 45s, do not shake the centrifuge tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fnej8","text":"Take out the ice bath and cool for 2 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ejsm6","text":"Add 800 µL of non-resistant LB medium preheated to 37°C to each tube, shake gently at 37°C, 150r/min for 1h.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2b30c","text":"Centrifugally concentrate to 100μL, spread it on an LB plate containing antibiotics, and incubate inverted at 37°C for 12-16h.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a8eel","text":"Make a negative control at the same time (use distilled water instead of plasmid).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7afcc","text":"Add 25ul of sterile water to the 96-well plate, pick about 15-20 colonies from the successfully transformed DH5α bacterial plate with a pipette tip, and mix them evenly. (Make a corresponding mark on the picking plate).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"40spe","text":"Put the mixed bacteria solution into 10ul to 200ul PCR tube and mark it.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"efsr0","text":"Take 0.1ul of bacterial solution in a 96-well plate and add it to the antibiotic-containing plate with a pipette tip and mark it.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
